<span id="freeTextContainer937065461927322320">I had a hard time getting into this book, but ended up really liking it. It is a multi-generational saga and, inevitably, I like one section better than the rest. I found Salome&apos;s story fascinating and I learned quite a bit about Urugayuan history in the process. All the characters were multi-dimensional rather than mere caricatures of political and personal positions.</span>
  <span id="freeText937065461927322320" style="display:none">I had a hard time getting into this book, but ended up really liking it. It is a multi-generational saga and, inevitably, I like one section better than the rest. I found Salome's story fascinating and I learned quite a bit about Urugayuan history in the process. All the characters were multi-dimensional rather than mere caricatures of political and personal positions.</span>
